      <div xml:id="NA118-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu paruvaṅ kaṇṭu āṟṟāḷāya talaivi colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what SHE said who was unable to bear it when seeing the season.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA118">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            aṭaikarai marāat talaṅkuciṉai poliyat</l>
<l>            taḷirkavi ṉeytiya taṇṇaṟum potumpiṟ</l>
<l>            cēvaloṭu keḻīiya ceṅka ṇiruṅkuyil</l>
<l>            pukaṉṟeti rālum pūmali kālaiyu</l>
<l>            makaṉṟōr maṉṟanam maṟantici ṉōreṉa </l>
<l>            viṇaruṟu puṭaivataṉ ṟalaiyum puṇarviṉai</l>
<l>            yōva mākka ḷoḷḷarak kūṭṭiya</l>
<l>            tukilikai yaṉṉa tuyttalaip pātiri</l>
<l>            vālita ḻalari vaṇṭupaṭa vēntip</l>
<l>            putumalar teruvutoṟu nuvalu </l>
<l>            notuma lāṭṭikku nōmeṉ ṉeñcē.</l>
    </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent">“Even at a time abounding in flowers, when the red-eyed dark Koel,</l>
<l rend="indent">united with [its] cock rejoices [and] dances face to face(?),</l>
<l rend="indent2">in the cool fragrant grove where the sprouts have attained beauty,</l>
<l rend="indent2">while the swaying branches of the Marā tree on the setling shore flourish,</l>
<l>he has departed indeed, he who has forgotten us”,</l>
<l rend="indent">on top of breaking [at this thought], perceiving the [flower] clusters,</l>
<l>my heart aches because of the strange woman<note place="foot">For the topos of the flower-selling woman cf. NA 97.</note></l>
<l rend="indent2">talking in every street of the new blossoms,</l>
<l rend="indent2">offering(?) for the bees to come pure-petalled oleander [and]</l>
<l rend="indent2">cotton-headed [blossoms of] the trumpet-flower trees, like brushes</l>
<l rend="indent3">dyed with bright vermilion by painters<note place="foot">Can we read <term xml:lang="ta">ōvamākkaḷ</term> as a variation of <term xml:lang="ta">ōvar</term>, "painter"?</note> in a work undertaken.</l>
        </lg>
